HEADWORD: Upstand
<hw>Up*stand"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To stand up; to
be erected; to rise.</def> <rj><au>Spenser. Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At once <qex>upstood</qex> the monarch, and <qex>upstood</qex>⟦br⟧
The wise Ulysses.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

